Last week, Erdogan had said Turkey has begun sending troops to Tripoli. 

He has also previously said Ankara would deploy troops. Speaking to reporters on a flight back from a Libya summit in Berlin, Erdogan said Turkey’s efforts at the summit had set the groundwork for a ceasefire between the warring parties, according to broadcaster NTV. 

He added that Turkey’s presence in the North African country increased hopes for peace.
--Reuters--